 tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530591\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530591\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ohx1665702678898.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ohx1665702678898.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ohx1665702678898.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ohx1665702678898\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define a Component Implementation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Each component can have one or more implementations.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__context_w5486ab1b5b1_w5487ab1b5_w5488ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__topic_d34001e1_d34002e1_d34003e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__p_d34004e1_d34005e1_d34006e1\">To define a component implementation:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17423e1_d17424e1_d17425e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Open the component signature in the Signature Editor.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17426e1_d17427e1_d17428e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span> adjacent to the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Implementations</span> field, then click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17429e1_d17430e1_d17431e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__p_d34007e1_d34008e1_d34009e1\">Select an implementation type in the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Type</span> field. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">The types available vary, depending on whether a Uniface or operating system\n                  implementation has already been selected, as well as and previously selected\n                  implementations. You cannot select both Uniface and operating system\n                  implementations at the same time.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17432e1_d17433e1_d17434e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To copy the description, comments, and associated keywords from the signature definition to the implementation definition, select the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Option</span> check box.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17435e1_d17436e1_d17437e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__p_d34010e1_d34011e1_d34012e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Properties</span> to define\n               the call-out properties of any implementation type other than Uniface or Java. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Call-out is not supported for Java, whereas call-out from one Uniface component to\n                  another requires no property settings.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__p_d34013e1_d34014e1_d34015e1\">For implementations that support both call-in\n                  and call-out, such as COM , the call-out mapping is also used as a basis for\n                  call-in.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__p_d34016e1_d34017e1_d34018e1\">For information on specific properties, press\n                     <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">F1</span>. </p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17438e1_d17439e1_d17440e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__p_d34019e1_d34020e1_d34021e1\">Optionally, for each implementation, define the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Description</span>, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Keyword</span>, and\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Comments</span> properties for the implementation. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Entering and saving values in these fields overrides any values copied from the\n               signature properties.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17441e1_d17442e1_d17443e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select the implementation you want to use as the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Default</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17444e1_d17445e1_d17446e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To delete an implementation:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17447e1_d17448e1_d17449e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Signature Editor, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span> adjacent to the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Implementations</span> field.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__li_d17450e1_d17451e1_d17452e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__p_d34022e1_d34023e1_d34024e1\">Select an implementation and click\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Delete</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">If more than one implementation has been specified for the current component\n                        and you delete the default implementation, the first implementation type in\n                        the list becomes the default.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"ohx1665702678898__note_w5489ab1b5b3c15b3b3b3b3_w5490ab1b5b3c15b3b3b3_w5491ab1b5b3c15b3b3_w5492ab1b5b3c15b3_w5493ab1b5b3c15_w5494ab1b5b3_w5495ab1b5_w5496ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> If you delete a Uniface implementation, the corresponding\n                        Uniface component is also deleted from the Uniface repository.</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kqj1665702890051.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Component Implementations</a><p>The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzx1665702678830.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define a Component Signature</a><p>Use the Signature Editor to create or modify component signatures. Signatures of Uniface components are automatically generated during compilation. Signatures of non-Uniface components can be created or imported.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530591\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530591\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define a Component Implementation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define a Component Implementation Each component can have one or more implementations. To define a component implementation: Open the component signature in the Signature Editor. Click >> adjacent to the Implementations field, then click New . Select an implementation type in the Type field. The types available vary, depending on whether a Uniface or operating system implementation has already been selected, as well as and previously selected implementations. You cannot select both Uniface and operating system implementations at the same time. To copy the description, comments, and associated keywords from the signature definition to the implementation definition, select the Option check box. Click Properties to define the call-out properties of any implementation type other than Uniface or Java. Call-out is not supported for Java, whereas call-out from one Uniface component to another requires no property settings. For implementations that support both call-in and call-out, such as COM , the call-out mapping is also used as a basis for call-in. For information on specific properties, press F1 . Optionally, for each implementation, define the Description , Keyword , and Comments properties for the implementation. Entering and saving values in these fields overrides any values copied from the signature properties. Select the implementation you want to use as the Default . To delete an implementation: In the Signature Editor, click >> adjacent to the Implementations field. Select an implementation and click Delete . If more than one implementation has been specified for the current component and you delete the default implementation, the first implementation type in the list becomes the default. CAUTION: If you delete a Uniface implementation, the corresponding Uniface component is also deleted from the Uniface repository. Related Links Component Implementations The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java. Define a Component Signature Use the Signature Editor to create or modify component signatures. Signatures of Uniface components are automatically generated during compilation. Signatures of non-Uniface components can be created or imported. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}